### Can we modify an attribute's value dynamically for an HTML tag? 

#### Answer

Yes. It is possible by using javascript using 'getElementById' method.
'<input type=“text” id=“inputField”>
document.getElementById(“inputField”).attr(“type”, “password”);'
Here we are changing type from 'text' to 'password'

#### Good to hear

* We can also use jQuery for this purpose using setAttribute() method.

##### Additional links

* [Reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/setAttribute)

